\title{cleanTMLE: Software Layer for an Outcome-Blind Staged Targeted-Learning Workflow}
\description{
Software infrastructure for an outcome-blind staged workflow for targeted-learning observational causal analyses on binary point-treatment studies. The package implements the staged-analysis framework of Muntner et al. (2024) by recording prespecification, design diagnostics, and a structured pre-outcome decision before the treatment-outcome association is examined. The tested v0.1 scope covers binary point exposure, binary outcome, and the marginal risk-difference estimand, with three estimator families: propensity- score matching, stabilised inverse-probability-of-treatment weighting, and targeted minimum loss-based estimation (TMLE), including simulation-selected TMLE via SuperLearner ensemble learning. The first methodological contribution is an outcome-blind plasmode candidate-selection procedure in which nuisance-parameter strategies are evaluated by oracle coverage on synthetic outcomes before real outcome access. The second is a prespecified data-quality stress test ('run_plasmode_dq_stress') that evaluates each candidate under covariate-missingness, treatment-misclassification, outcome- misclassification, and unmeasured-confounding scenarios, producing a degradation gradient on the same performance scale as the baseline plasmode metrics. Together, the two screens produce a pre-outcome study dossier that a review team can examine before authorising the primary analysis. Time-to-event helpers (IPW risk curves, g-computation, augmented IPW, IPW hazard ratios, survival TMLE via 'survtmle', and longitudinal TMLE via 'lmtp') are experimental extensions outside the tested v0.1 scope.
}
